Prep the ingredients: Bring a large #pot{} of water with @salt{large pinch} to a boil. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%clove}. Strip the @thyme{1/4%ounce} from the stem and roughly chop the leaves. Finely chop the @sage{1/4%ounce}. Juice the @lemon{1}. Trim, halve and thinly slice the @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} into shreds.

> Orecchiette means "little ears" in Italian and is great for holding delicious sauces.

Cook the vegetables: Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the @Mixed Wild Mushrooms{4%ounce} to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until golden brown. Add the Brussels sprouts and cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until softened and slightly golden brown. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and set aside.

Cook the pasta: Add the @Orecchiette Pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{8-10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving ½ cup of the pasta water.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in the same pan you cooked the vegetables in over medium-high heat. Add the @Pancetta{4%ounce} and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until golden brown and crispy. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Make the sauce: Add the garlic, sage, and thyme to the pan with the pancetta and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, and ½ cup pasta water to the pan. Bring to a simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}, until slightly thickened. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Toss the drained pasta, Brussels sprouts, mushrooms, and half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/2%ounce} into the pan with the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Serve the pasta with the remaining @Parmesan Cheese{1/2%ounce} on top and enjoy!